doc.after: The contract for the Batch 1 aircraft was signed on 29 July 1976.[16] The first aircraft were delivered to the RAF and German Air Force on 5 and 6 June 1979 respectively.[26] The first Italian Tornado was delivered on 25 September 1981. On 29 January 1981, the Tri-national Tornado Training Establishment (TTTE) officially opened at RAF Cottesmore, remaining active in training pilots from all operating nations until 31 March 1999.[27] The 500th Tornado to be produced was delivered to West Germany on 19 December 1987.[28]
